ce:section.ce:para:
Both the bare and passivated CDs can be excited in a wide range (from 260nm to 500nm), but emitting at similar wavelength when excited from 260nm to 400nm (not shown here) and emitting a little different for the others (as shown in Fig. 2
                        ). Their maximal excitations were near 470nm, while maximal emissions were near 520nm (as shown in Fig. 3
                        ). After passivated with PEG1500N, the fluorescence of CDs increased, which indicates successful conjugation of PEG to CDs. Since the fluorescence intensity of PEG at same conditions was very weak compared to passivated CDs, we can believe that the increase of fluorescence intensity is due to the passivation progress rather than PEG itself.
